The giant strike forces are coming together
The League Unions and the National Federation of Labour Commissions will constitute on Friday a strike commission to coordinate the Monday strike that will last indefinitely.
On Saturday there will be a protest rally, while Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - work will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since the railway transit will be completely stopped and until 1 p.m. the workers of the Collective Transport Company of Budapest will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike, which will be held jointly with the National Federation of Labour Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Engineers' Union will also be set up to coordinate the actions of Monday.
On Saturday there will be a protest rally, while on Monday the participating unions will strike for indefinite time, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their appeal for strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the Monday agenda of the National Assembly it is also possible to vote only on the public health law at very late night hours, or at best near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will have to be significant difficulties in transport: railways will stop working indefinitely, in the morning a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the urban bus transport of the companies Volán will have to be stopped.
At the same time, there will be a closing of half of the roads in many parts of the country.
Many unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League website.
Some unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for defined time.
Until Thursday afternoon the State Railway and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) were unable to reach an agreement or even about the minimum services, although, as Christmas parties approach, more and more people travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1 p.m., workers of the Collective Transport Company of Budapest, Budapest airports from 7 a.m. to 9 a.m., will hold a four-hour strike by the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the Educators' Unions called for a 2 a.m. strike and the Democratic Trade Union of Educators from 2 to 8 a.m.
The Hungarian Association of Doctors will be on a national strike at alternative times and the Social and Health Workers' Democratic Union (SDTSSS) which are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal on public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is to gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation which will enter into force next year.
The third is to ensure, even before 2010, that in the case of advanced pensions the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) that is part of the League Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division) of the Political Capital Division, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August of this year with the support of the Movement by a Better Hungary, has, from several points of view, increased the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the Hungarian Guard's activity the highest political risk is that "with the worsening ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsy population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic confrontations may occur".
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocative event of this nature - the representative of the research institute added.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main flaws of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Roma problem to representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians".
This exacerbates the problem, prevents normal dialogue, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they believe.
Moreover, according to the research institute, the National Guard activity, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
