The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law defines precisely the days that are written with red numbers on the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that the coming year will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Even in the EU or North America, parties are not united.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national party, state party and festive days.
The holidays are fundamentally related to religious festivals and historical ephemeral events.
Let us celebrate the New Year also: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter above all so that those who have spent celebrating the old year can rest.
All year round we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is national feast on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23rd, commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20, we celebrate the foundation of the State, on May 1st, the festival of work, on November 1st and 2nd, we remind our deceased family and friends.
Also, in our country are two-day parties the Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when before or after the holiday there is only one work day.
In exchange for extended weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
He is the minister of labour who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the party.
This legal rule is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
It is not mandatory, however, for companies and service institutions which, because of their role, work uninterruptedly even during public holidays.
This year the work order can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24 it almost stops life in the country, since according to the experiences, most people "make bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
Next year several of our parties will coincide with mid- or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
The agenda will first be modified around the work party so that, for four successive days, workers can rest.
On Saturday, April 26th, it will be a work day, so that on Friday, May 2nd it will be a holiday.
The other change relates to the party on October 23rd: on Saturday, October 18th, you will have to work instead of Friday 24th.
On the other hand, the year that comes during the end of the year party you can rest, since from 24 December you will not work anywhere, nor even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
