What's the insurance for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible injuries, is an important expense that will depend on various factors such as age, sex, age of the car, marital status, type of vehicle to ensure or use it, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we must be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured one.
This undertaking is materialized in an insurance contract, which provides that the company receives the value of the premium agreed in exchange for being held liable for the obligation to pay the compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of meat, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use it is given, among others.
Insurance companies establish their prices according to statistics, so that to the greater likelihood of an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
It is for this reason that both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics reflect that they have a lower rate of sinisterity due to their prudence.
Similarly, by handing out the accounts, companies have come to the conclusion that married persons tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency and thus the probability of having some kind of perchance.
Increasing the frequency increases the odds.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver must study the situation well to choose that car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age are faced with various disadvantages in hiring insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and old age.
Although the ideal to be well assured is a risk-free insurance, there are other more economical options.
Precautionary drivers can opt for a complete risk with frankness, so they get insurance coverage at full risk but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would assume that the customer pays a portion of the amount of the sinister.
"The portion of the amount of the amount the customer provides will be pre-established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount," says Luis Noguera, the highest responsible in Spain of First Europe, online insurance broker.
Another option is an extended third party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not to those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A tip.
If you are under 25 years of age try to be careful and avoid the claims as far as possible, as this will affect the bonus, being able to reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate owned by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is a charge on that basic tariff.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year it can be allowed to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After the 25-year-old band drivers have it easier to hire insurance, since the rate of sinnestrality is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended thing is to hire a whole risk with frankness.
"Young people are not usually able to make use of the experience previously gained when you are in an accident, and even when driving", says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'feel of the novice' has passed.
However, if the customer is married but still has no children, it is preferable that he negotiates a insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation permits him, of course.
For its part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest rate of sinnestrality, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with franchise (may be this of 300 euros), or, when there is a high level of bonus, one to third increased from the third year of life of the vehicle.
"They carry out a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to allow themselves the luxury of taking on a greater amount of franchise," Luis Noguera says.
For retirees, an insurance at all risk is recommended with franchise (which is EUR 150), or one to third parties is extended when a high level of bonus is achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver before possible claims, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
